# Debugging Rules

## Frontend Error Handling

```ts
// ✅ Always parse API errors with the shared helper
import { parseApiError } from "@/src/lib/api-helpers";

try {
  await updateLead({ id, data });
  toast.success("Status updated!");
} catch (err) {
  toast.error(parseApiError(err));
}
```

```ts
// ✅ TanStack mutation error handling
const { mutateAsync } = useUpdateLead();
return useMutation({
  mutationFn: ...,
  onSuccess: () => toast.success("Saved"),
  onError: (err) => toast.error(parseApiError(err)),
});
```

## Backend Error Handling

```ts
// ✅ Throw in service, catch in error-handler middleware
// service:
if (!lead) throw new Error("Lead not found");

// route — just check and return 404 for known not-found cases:
const lead = await getLeadById(id);
if (!lead) { res.status(404).json({ error: "Not found" }); return; }
```

## Auth Errors (401)

The `apiAxios` interceptor in `lib/api-helpers/axios-instance.ts` automatically:
1. Catches 401 responses
2. Attempts `POST /api/auth/refresh`
3. Retries the original request with new token
4. If refresh fails → redirects to `ROUTES.LOGIN`

Do NOT manually handle 401 in individual components.

## Loading States

```tsx
// ✅ Always show loading skeleton
if (isLoading) return (
  <div className="space-y-3 animate-pulse">
    {[1,2,3].map(i => <div key={i} className="h-20 bg-[#f7f4ef] rounded-2xl" />)}
  </div>
);
```

## Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `toast({ title: "..." })` | `toast.success("...")` |
| `catch (e) {}` | Always log or show toast |
| 401 in admin but no redirect | Check `apiAxios` interceptor is wired |
| `data?.leads` undefined crash | Check `isLoading` guard before render |
